'''Derek Jenkins''' is a former [[Visual arts education|teacher]] and retired [[Painting|artist]] known primarily for his paintings of [[Cornwall|Cornish]] landscapes and paintings of striped [[pebble]]s found on beaches throughout the county.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.ca/books?redir_esc=y&id=4VdIAQAAIAAJ&dq=St+Ives,+1883-1993:+Portrait+of+an+Art+Colony.+London&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Derek+Jenkins|title=St Ives, 1883-1993: Portrait of an Art Colony|last=Whybrow|first=Marion|date=1994|publisher=Antique Collectors' Club|year=|isbn=9781851491704|location=|pages=185|language=en}}</ref> His best known work is 'South from Cape Cornwall' which was exhibited in the [[Tate St Ives|Tate]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.wave7gallery.co.uk/Derek%20Jenkins.htm |title=Derek Jenkins biography  |date=2017-09-30 |website=wave7gallery.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.wave7gallery.co.uk/Derek%20Jenkins_files/image002.jpg |title=Wave 7 Gallery - Paintings |date=2017-09-30 |website=wave7gallery.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.campdengallery.co.uk/displayart.php?rid=78&aid=375&tid=1|title=Campden Gallery|website=www.campdengallery.co.uk|accessdate=26 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.campdengallery.co.uk/displayartists.php?rid=78&tid=1|title=Campden Gallery|website=www.campdengallery.co.uk|accessdate=26 August 2017}}</ref>

He was born in [[Cardiff, Wales]] {{Circa|1937}}. He went on to study art at the [[West of England College of Art]] in [[Bristol|Bristol, United Kingdom]]. He completed his teaching diploma at the [[London University]]. In 1972 he moved from [[London]] to [[Truro, Cornwall]] where he was the Head of the Art Department at [[Falmouth School of Art]] for 17 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cornwallartists.org/cornwall-artists/derek-jenkins|title=Derek JENKINS - cornwall artists index|website=cornwallartists.org|accessdate=26 August 2017}}</ref>

After his retirement from teaching in 1989, he pursued his own artistic works, which have been exhibited in the [[Tate St Ives]] and locally, in [[Falmouth, Cornwall|Falmouth]] and [[St Ives, Cornwall|St Ives]] art galleries. He was a member of the [[Newlyn Society of Artists]] during their centenary year and was a member of the Penwith Society of Artists. He retired from painting in 2005, aged 68.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newcraftsmanstives.com/index.php?location=artist&artist=163|title=The New Craftsman Gallery - St. Ives - Cornwall - Derek Jenkins|website=www.newcraftsmanstives.com|accessdate=26 August 2017}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{cite book|title=Falmouth Art Gallery 20 Years of Contemporary Art at Falmouth Art Gallery 1980-2000}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=RCM & RIC Three Spires Festival Exhibition of Paintings, Sculpture and Pottery, Truro (Opening of the RCM or County Art Gallery, by the Royal Institution of Cornwall)}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Hardie (1995) 100 Years in Newlyn: Diary of a Gallery (List of NSA Members at Centennial)}}</ref>

