{{Infobox person | name = Toby Onwumere | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1990|02|01}} <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = | other_names = | alma_mater = [[University of California, San Diego]] | occupation = [[Actor]] | years_active = 2016-present | known_for = Sense8 | notable_works = ''[[Sense8]]'' }}
'''Toby Onwumere''' is an actor known for the role of Capheus on the second season of the [[Netflix]] original series ''[[Sense8]]''.<ref name=DL>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/sense8-aml-ameen-toby-onwumere-recasting-wachowski-netflix-series-1201744886/ |title='Sense8': Aml Ameen Replaced By Toby Onwumere In Wachowskis' Netflix Series |date=April 26, 2016 |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |author1=Andreeva, Nellie |author2=Fleming Jr, Mike |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=April 27, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507132635/http://deadline.com/2016/04/sense8-aml-ameen-toby-onwumere-recasting-wachowski-netflix-series-1201744886/ |archivedate=May 7, 2016 |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2016/12/sense8-capheus-recast-toby-onwumere-season-2-lana-wachowski-1201763899/|title=Sense8: How Toby Onwumere, Season 2’s New Capheus, Joined the Sensates - IndieWire|last=Miller|first=Liz Shannon|date=December 26, 2016|website=|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/14/arts/television/sense8-a-christmas-special-is-coming-to-netflix.html|title=‘Sense8: A Christmas Special’ Is Coming to Netflix|date=14 December 2016|work=The New York Times}}</ref>
== Early life == Onwumere was born on February 1, 1990. Prior to being cast in ''Sense8'', Onwumere graduated from [[University of California, San Diego]]'s graduate acting program with an MFA.<ref name="DL" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://theatre.ucsd.edu/Showcase/Actors/2015/TOnwumere/index.html|title=UCSD Theatre & Dance: Actors Showcase 2015: Toby Onwumere|last=|first=|date=|website=Department of Theatre & Dance|publisher=University of California, San Diego|access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref> He completed his undergraduate acting training at the [[University of Evansville]] in Indiana.
== Career ==
=== Stage === Onwumere has appeared on stage with [[Santa Cruz Shakespeare]] where he played [[Macduff (Macbeth)|Macduff]] in [[Macbeth]] and Cleton in [[The Liar (Corneille play)|The Liar]]. He also appeared in the previous incarnation of the festival; [[Shakespeare Santa Cruz]] Where he played in [[The Taming of the Shrew]] and [[Henry V (play)|Henry V]]
=== Screen === Onwumere replaced British actor Aml Ameen, who played the role of Capheus in season 1 of ''Sense8''.<ref name="DL" /> Onwumere made his debut as Capheus on the December 2016 Christmas special of ''Sense8''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/sense8-debuts-new-capheus-actor-fans-react-recasting-2465834|title=‘Sense8’ Debuts New Capheus Actor; Fans React To Recasting|last=Massabrook|first=Nicole|date=2016-12-27|work=[[International Business Times]]|access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref> He has also been cast to reoccur in the Fifth Season of Fox's Empire, as a war correspondent and love interest of Jamal Lyon.
